ault": false, "description": "Area: const generics (parameters and arguments)"}, {"id": 1486687397, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxNDg2Njg3Mzk3", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/F-const_generics", "name": "F-const_generics", "color": "f9c0cc", "default": false, "description": "`#![feature(const_generics)]`"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 53, "created_at": "2020-07-23T20:06:00Z", "updated_at": "2021-05-04T17:01:05Z", "closed_at": "2021-05-04T17:01:04Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "example by @felix91gr \r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(const_generics)]\r\n#![allow(const_err)]\r\n\r\nfn foo<const C: u8>() {\r\n  if C > 0 {\r\n    println!(\"Foo gives {}\", 25 / C);\r\n  }\r\n  else {\r\n    println!(\"Foo gives 0\");\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n  foo::<0>();\r\n}\r\n```\r\nNote that this currently requires `allow(const_err)` because `25 /C` would panic at runtime.\r\nThis is however fine as it isn't reachable because of `C > 0`.\r\n\r\nWe probably should relax this slightly here, not sure what's the best approach though\r\n\r\n**Other example (by @RalfJung)**\r\n```rust\r\nconst D: u8 = 0; // imagine this is in a different crate\r\n\r\npub fn foo() {\r\n    if D > 0 {\r\n        let _val = 25/D; // ERROR\r\n    } else {\r\n        panic!()\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "lcnr", "id": 29864074, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI5ODY0MDc0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/29864074?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lcnr", "html_url": "https://github.com/lcnr", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lcnr/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lcnr/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lcnr/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lcnr/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/